@node RenderToBack "RenderToBack"

RENDER2BACK (2.0)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RenderToBack
      Render2Back

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Pushes the current render screen to the back, if possible. If there
      is no render screen, nothing happens.  Some render screens cannot be
      moved this way, such as OpalVision and IV24.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
      RenderToFront

@endnode

@node RenderToFront "RenderToFront"

RENDER2FRONT (2.0)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RenderToFront
      Render2Front

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Brings the current render screen to the front.  If there is no render
      screen, nothing happens.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
      RenderToBack

@endnode

@node Requesters "Requesters"

REQUESTERS

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Requesters On/S,Off/S,PubScreen/K

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Enable or disable error requesters.  Also sets the public screen
      where requesters are shown.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}On,Off@{uu}
	 Enable or disable error requesters.  If disabled, requesters will
	 not be shown to notify the user of errors.

      @{u}PubScreen (2.0)@{uu}
	 Sets the name of the public screen where requesters are shown
	 (includes boolean, string, integer, complex, and list requesters).

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node RequestFile "RequestFile"

REQUESTFILE

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RequestFile Title/A,Path,File,Pattern

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Display a file requester from which the user can select filename.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Title@{uu}
	 Title to appear in the titlebar of the requester.

      @{u}Path@{uu}
	 Initial pathname to go in the path gadget.

      @{u}File@{uu}
	 Initial filename to go in the file gadget.

      @{u}Pattern@{uu}
	 Initial pattern to go in the pattern gadget.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Full pathname of selected file, if not cancelled.

      New for 2.0:  The Arexx variables FILEREQ.FILE, FILEREQ.PATH, and
      FILEREQ.PAT are set to the selected file, path, and pattern of the
      requester if successful.

@endnode

@node RequestNotify "RequestNotify"

REQUESTNOTIFY

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RequestNotify Prompt/A/F

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Display an information requester to the user.  The user must click
      the Okay gadget to proceed.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Prompt@{uu}
	 Text in the body of the requester.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node RequestNumber "RequestNumber"

REQUESTNUMBER

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RequestNumber Prompt/A,Default/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Display a number requester to the user.  The user must enter a number
      and hit Okay or Cancel to proceed.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Prompt@{uu}
	 Title of the requester.

      @{u}Default@{uu}
	 Default starting value of the requester.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns the number the user entered if successful.

@endnode

@node RequestResponse "RequestResponse"

REQUESTRESPONSE

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RequestResponse Prompt/A/F

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Display a boolean (yes/No) requester to the user; Okay and Cancel
      gadgets will appear at the bottom of the requester.  The user must
      click one of the gadgets to proceed.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Prompt@{uu}
	 Text to appear in the body of the requester.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Non-zero return code if the user chooses Cancel; zero if he chooses
      Okay.

@endnode

@node RequestSlider "RequestSlider"

REQUESTSLIDER

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RequestSlider Prompt/A,Lowest/N,Highest/N,Default/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Display a slider requester to the user, allowing a choice of number
      within a distinct range.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Prompt@{uu}
	 Prompt string; the title of the requester.

      @{u}Lowest,Highest@{uu}
	 Range of values allowed in the slider gadget.

      @{u}Default@{uu}
	 Initial starting value of the slider gadget.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns the number selected by the user if successful.

@endnode

@node RequestString "RequestString"

REQUESTSTRING

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RequestString Prompt/A,Default

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Display a string requester to the user, the user must enter a string
      or press Cancel to proceed.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Prompt@{uu}
	 Title of the string requester.

      @{u}Default@{uu}
	 Default starting string to go in the requester.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns the string entered if successful.

@endnode

@node RGBToOther "RGBToOther"

RGBTOOTHER (2.0)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RGBToOther Mode/N/A,Red/N/A,Green/N/A,Blue/N/A
      RGB2Other Mode/N/A,Red/N/A,Green/N/A,Blue/N/A

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Convert an RGB color to a different colorspace.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Mode@{uu}
	 Colorspace to convert to:

	 0 = RGB
	    1 = HSV
	    2 = CMY
	    3 = CMYK
	    4 = YIQ
	    5 = YUV

      @{u}Red,Green,Blue@{uu}
	 RGB color to convert.	Values range from 0-255.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns the converted color in RESULT in one of the following forms:

	 HSV:  "<hue:0-359> <sat:0-255> <val:0-255>"
	    CMY:  "<cya:0-255> <mag:0-255> <yel:0-255>"
	    CMYK: "<cya:0-100> <mag:0-100> <yel:0-100> <black:0-100>"
	    YIQ:  "<luma> <i> <q>"
	    YUV:  "<luma> <u> <v>"

   @{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
      OtherToRGB

@endnode

@node RIP "RIP"

RIP

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RIP Threshold/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Perform a remove isolated pixels function on the current image or
      region.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Threshold@{uu}
