@node Rotate "Rotate"

ROTATE

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Rotate Angle/N,Red/N,Green/N,Blue/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Rotate the current image by a specified angle.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Angle@{uu}
	 Number of degrees of clockwise rotation.  Negative numbers
	 indicate counter-clockwise rotation, posisitive numbers indicate
	 clockwise rotation.  The special case of -90, 90, and 180 are
	 handled much faster than other arbitrary angles.  Fractional
	 values are accepted.

      @{u}Red,Green,Blue (2.0)@{uu}
	 Specifies the background color (defaults to 0 0 0).

      Note:  If no arguments are given, the standard Rotate window is
	 presented.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node Roughen "Roughen"

ROUGHEN

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Roughen Amount/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Perform a roughening effect on the current image or region.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Amount@{uu}
	 Amount of roughening to apply (1-255).  If not given, a requester
	 will be presented.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node Rx "Rx"

RX

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Rx Async/S,Quiet/S,Command,Args/F

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Invoke an Arexx macro.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Async@{uu}
	 If specified, the macro will be run as separate task, and this
	 command will return immediately.  Most of the time you will not
	 need to use this.  Make sure that you stop the macro before
	 exiting ImageFX.  If the macro is not run asynchronously, the RX
	 command will not return until the macro is finished.

      @{u}Quiet@{uu}
	 If specified, the "arexx macro in progress" window will not be
	 shown.

      @{u}Command@{uu}
	 Arexx command to run.	If not given, a file requester will be
	 presented.

      @{u}Args (2.1)@{uu}
	 Arguments to be supplied to the command.  As of ImageFX 2.1, the
	 arguments are decoded separately from the command.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
      RXS

@endnode

@node RxHalt "RxHalt"

RXHALT

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      RxHalt Global/S

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Halt any and all asynchronous Arexx programs launched by the program.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Global@{uu}
	 If specified, the global Arexx HALT flag is set, which will stop
	 ALL executing Arexx processes, no matter who started them.  You
	 generally shouldn't have to use this.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node Rxs "Rxs"

RXS

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Rxs Command/F/A

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Invoke an Arexx "string program".

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Command@{uu}
	 String program to run.  The entire contents are taken as an Arexx
	 program and are passed to the Arexx interpretor for processing.
	 The string may contain any valid Arexx commands.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node Saturation "Saturation"

SATURATION

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Saturation Adjust/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Adjust the saturation of the current image or region.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Adjust@{uu}
	 Amount to adjust the saturation (-127 to +127).

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node SaveAlphaAs "SaveAlphaAs"

SAVEALPHAAS

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      SaveAlphaAs Format,File,Args/F

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Save the current alpha channel to a file using a specified file
      format.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Format@{uu}
	 File format in which to save the alpha channel.  If not given, a
	 scrolling list of choices will be presented.

      @{u}File@{uu}
	 Name of the file to save the alpha channel as.  If not given, a
	 file requester will be presented.  If a full path is not given,
	 the file will be saved to the current alpha channel save path (as
	 set in prefs).

      @{u}Args@{uu}
	 Arguments passed to the saver module.	See the documentation of
	 the particular saver module in question.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node SaveBrushAs "SaveBrushAs"

SAVEBRUSHAS

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      SaveBrushAs Format,File,Args/F

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Save the current brush, using the requested file format.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Format@{uu}
	 File format in which to save the brush.  If not given, a scrolling
	 list of choices will be presented.

      @{u}File@{uu}
	 Filename of the output image.	If not given, a file requester will
	 be presented to the user.  If “Create Icons?” in Prefs is turned
	 on, the default brush icon will also be saved with the image.	If
	 a full pathname is not given, then the fill be saved to the
	 current Brush path (as set in Prefs).

      @{u}Args@{uu}
	 Arguments passed to the saver module.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node SaveBufferAs "SaveBufferAs"

SAVEBUFFERAS

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      SaveBufferAs Format,File,Force/S,Args/F

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Save the current image buffer, using the requested file format.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Format@{uu}
	 File format to save file in.  If not given, a scrolling list of
	 choices will be presented.

      @{u}File@{uu}
	 Name of the file in which to save the image.  If “Create Icons?”
	 in Prefs is on, an icon will be saved with the image.	If no file
	 is given, a file requester will be presented to the user.  If a
	 full path is not given, then the file will be saved in the current
	 buffer save path (as set in Prefs).

      @{u}Force@{uu}
	 If given, this will overwrite existing files without prompting the
	 user.

      @{u}Args@{uu}
	 Passed to the saver module that gets called.  See the
	 documentation for the various saver modules.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node SaveMaskAs "SaveMaskAs"

SAVEMASKAS (2.0)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      SaveMaskAs File

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Save the currently defined region to disk.  Currently the region is
      always saved as an IFF ILBM file.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}File@{uu}
	 Name of the disk file to save to.  If not provided, a requester is
	 presented.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
      LoadMask

@endnode

@node SavePaletteAs "SavePaletteAs"

SAVEPALETTEAS

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      SavePaletteAs File,Number/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Save the current palette to a file on disk, including range
      information if possible.	Currently palettes may only be saved as
      ILBM files.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}File@{uu}
	 Name of the file to store the palette in.  If not given, a file
	 requester will be presented.  If a full path is not given, the
	 file will be saved to the current Palette path (as set in prefs).

      @{u}Number (1.50)@{uu}
	 Palette number to save.  -1 to save the currently displayed
	 palette, or a palette number ranging from 1 - 8.  (Palette 8 is
	 the render palette.)

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node SavePrefsAs "SavePrefsAs"

SAVEPREFSAS (2.0)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      SavePrefsAs File

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Save the current preferences settings to a given disk file.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}File@{uu}
	 Name of the file to store the preferences in.	If not given, a
	 file requester will be presented.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node SavePreviewAs "SavePreviewAs"

SAVEPREVIEWAS

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      SavePreviewAs Format,File,Args/F

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Save the current preview screen to a file, in the file format
      specified.  This is basically just a screen grab of the preview
      screen.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Format@{uu}
	 File format to save in; if not specfied, a save format requester
	 will be presented.

      @{u}File@{uu}
	 Filename to store the image in.  If not specified, a file
	 requester will be presented.  If a full path is not given, the
	 file will be saved in the current rendered image save path (as
	 defined in prefs).

      @{u}Args@{uu}
	 Arguments passed to the Saver module.	See the documentation for
	 the various saver modules.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node SaveRenderedAs "SaveRenderedAs"

SAVERENDEREDAS

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      SaveRenderedAs Format,File,Args/F

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Save the current rendered image to a file, in the file format
      specified.  Note that some render modules to do support saveable
      files (Firecracker render, for example).	In this case, nothing will
      be saved.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Format@{uu}
	 File format to save in; if not specified, a save format requester
	 will be presented to the user.

      @{u}File@{uu}
	 Filename to store the rendered image in.  If not specified, a file
	 requester will be presented.  If a full path is not given, the
	 file will be saved to the current rendered image path (as set in
	 prefs).

      @{u}Args@{uu}
	 Passed to the saver module that gets called.  See the
	 documentation for the various saver modules.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node SaveUndo "SaveUndo"

SAVEUNDO

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      SaveUndo Left/N,Top/N,Width/N,Height/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Save an area of the main image buffer to the undo buffer, for later
      retreival via. the Undo function.

      Normally, functions that destroy the image automatically save the
      area affected to the undo buffer, but you might want to explicitly
      control when and where the undo gets saved.  For example, if you do a
      long series of processes, the undo will be saved at each step, so
      that if the user does an undo after it’s all over he’ll only restore
      the last step done.  But if you use SaveUndo at the beginning of the
      series and then turn the undo off during the series, you will have a
      copy of the original buffer in the undo buffer.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Left@{uu}
	 Left edge (in buffer pixels) of area to save.

      @{u}Top@{uu}
	 Top Edge (in buffer pixels) of area to save.

      @{u}Width@{uu}
	 Width (in buffer pixels) of area to save.

      @{u}Height@{uu}
	 Height (in buffer pixels) of area to save.

      Note:  If no arguments are given, the entire buffer is saved.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node Scale "Scale"

SCALE

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Scale Width/N,Height/N,Percent/S,Fast/S,Border/S,%/S,Smooth/S

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Scale the current image buffer to a new size.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Width,Height@{uu}
	 New size of the buffer in pixels.

      @{u}Percent, %@{uu}
	 Indicates that the width and height are given as percentages
	 instead of absolute pixel sizes.

      @{u}Fast@{uu}
	 Use the fast scaling method, which does not do any anti-aliasing.

      @{u}Border@{uu}
	 Use the border scale method.

      @{u}Smooth@{uu} (3.1b)
	 Use the smooth scale method.

      Note:  If no arguments are given, the standard Scale window is
	 presented.  If no scaling method is given, Accurate scaling
	 is assumed.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node Scanner "Scanner"

SCANNER

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Scanner Command/A,Args/F

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Send a command to the current Scanner module.  It is entirely up to
      the module to interpret the command.  See the documentation for the
      individual scanner modules for details of available commands and
      their results.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Depends on the command.@{uu}

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Depends on the command.

@endnode

@node Scissors "Scissors"

SCISSORS

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Scissors

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Initiate a brush cut operation.  Issuing this command places the
      program into brush cut mode; you must then follow with a standard
      drawing command to cut out a brush in that shape.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
      MagicScissors

@endnode

