@node Text "Text"

TEXT (OBSOLETE)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Text Font,Size/N,Aspect/N,Text/F

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Create a text string, using the selected font name and size.  The
      text is made into a brush.  This command is provided for backwards
      compatibility reason; see the Text hook for more detailed text
      creation tools.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Font@{uu}
	 Name of the font to use in building the text.	If not given, it
	 uses the last font used.  Be sure to include the ".font" extension
	 on the end of the font name, eg. "topaz.font".

      @{u}Size@{uu}
	 Height of the font in pixels.	Under 2.0, the chosen font will be
	 scaled to your chosen size.  Under 1.3, the nearest existing size
	 will be used.

      @{u}Aspect@{uu}
	 Under Kickstart 2.0, this controls the aspect ratio of the font.
	 The value given is a percentage representing the amount to scale
	 the width of the font.  For example, a value of 100 is standard,
	 50 is half normal width, and 200 is twice normal width.

      @{u}Text@{uu}
	 The actual string of text to use in creating the brush.

      Note:  If no arguments are specified, the program will go into
	 the Text menu.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node Transparency "Transparency"

TRANSPARENCY

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Transparency Include/N,Exclude/N,Closeness/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Select the current include and exclude transparency color ranges,
      along with the color closeness.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Include@{uu}
	 Color range to be included in all subsequent processes.  Should be
	 in the range 0 - 8, where 0 disables the include range entirely.

      @{u}Exclude@{uu}
	 Color range to be excluded in all subsequent processes.  Should be
	 in the range of 0 - 8, where 0 disables the exclude range
	 entirely.

      @{u}Closeness@{uu}
	 Color closeness to apply to the selected color ranges.  Should be
	 in the range 1 - 255.

      Note:  If no arguments are given, no change is made.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns the previous transparency settings, before any changes, in
      the form "IncludeRange ExcludeRange Closeness".

@endnode

